Name: Square
Description: Four equal sides and four 90 degree angles.

Name: Rectangle
Description: Four 90 angles and two sets of equal parallel sides.

Name: Rhombus
Description: A shape with four equal sides, where opposite sides are parallel. Opposite angles are equal but adjacent angles cannot be equal (or else it is a square).

Name: Kite
Description: A shape with two pairs of equal sides where the pairs are adjacent to eachother.

Name: Circle
Description: A round shape where each pair of opposite points have the same distance (e.g. diameter).

Name: Ellipse
Description: A curved object that looks like a circle that was stretched across one axis.

Name: Crescent
Description: A curved shape that represents the intersection of two arcs.

Name: Equilateral
Description: A traingle with three equal sides and three equal angles.

Name: Isosceles Triangle
Description: A triangle with two equal side and two equal angles.

Name: Right Angle Triangle
Description: A triangle with one angle that equals 90 degrees.

Name: Cube
Description: A three dimensional object with 6 square faces (like a box).

Name: Cylinder
Description: A three dimensional object with two parallel circle faces.
